author: COMSOL
description: This example shows how to model a deep excavation. The main application area of that kind of models is civil engineering. In this case, the in situ lateral pressure acting on the retaining wall during the excavation of the soil is modeled with boundary loads. The soil assumes Drucker–Prager plasticity.
